RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 98. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AUSPICIOUS STYLE stalked the decent early pace, saved all of the ground while well placed through the backstretch run, inched closer along the second turn, mounted a rail bid in upper stretch, vied for the lead at the furlong marker, took command into the final stages, dug in while under pressure in deep stretch and lasted for the win. WINE AND WHISKY settled three wide in the early running, gained ground heading to the half-mile marker, ran in pursuit of the pacesetter while two wide on the far turn, shifted three wide for the drive, rallied inside of the furlong pole, pressured AUSPICIOUS STYLE in deep stretch but could not get by the determined winner and missed for the win, while holding for the place. IL CAPITANO assumed command leaving the break and dictated terms in the early stages, set decent fractions to the half-mile marker, was well handled into the far turn, came under pressure at the furlong grounds, met the bid of AUSPICIOUS STYLE to the sixteenth-marker, vied between runners into deep stretch and weakened in the final stages, while clear of the rest for third. ECOLOGIST took back and rated off of the early pace while saving ground, was well positioned through the backstretch run, chased along the far turn, ran evenly to the furlong marker and lacked a late rally. SUGAR BEETS settled two wide in the early stages, raced between rivals while not far back through the backstretch run, chased two wide and between runners to the quarter marker, swung three wide for the stretch drive and did not produce a late response. SUNNY SPOT settled outside of rivals in the early running, improved position along the backstretch run and made a three wide middle move nearing the half-mile marker, raced three wide along the far turn and came four wide into the stretch, could not keep pace in the final furlong and tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside,well placed,rail bid 1/8,dug in late,lasted

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (If a Cal-Bred Wins This Race, The Owner Will Receive a $10,000 Incentive Award Directly From The California Thoroughbred Breeders' Association.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOMER WELLS broke alertly and assumed command at the start, set a mildly pressured pace into the turn and was well rated to the quarter marker while carving out moderate fractions, shook free into the stretch, was kept to task under steady urging to the sixteenth-marker, came under late pressure from HAYWOOD and lasted in a drive to prevail. HAYWOOD was away a step slowly from the gate and tracked the early pace from the rear, improved position on the turn while outside of rivals, came four wide into the lane and closed to come within aim at the furlong marker, closed willingly in deep stretch and just missed for the win, while besting the rest. LIGHT DRAGOON was allowed to settle in the early running, raced two wide into the turn then swung three deep for the drive, closed well inside of the furlong marker and held clearly in the end for third. RIGHT HAND RYDER was forwardly placed leaving the break and mildly pressed the early pace while outside of HOMER WELLS, kept close attendance through the turn, lost position at the furlong marker and weakened in deep stretch. ELEGANT BOY chased the pace from the inside, lost ground on the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and lacked a late response. NO SHOW JONES chased the decent early pace from the second flight, came two wide to the quarter marker, could not keep pace into the stretch and tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off step slow,3wide turn,4wide rally stretch,just missed,2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Light Dragoon
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled early,2wide turn,3wide into stretch,closed well,clear 3rd

ENTRY.NAME: Elegant Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,lost ground turn,evenly to 1/8,no late response

ENTRY.NAME: Homer Wells
ENTRY.COMMENT: off well,set pace,well rated,shook free 1/8,kept to task,lasted

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 98. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $62,500. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOIC LUNA rated off of the moderate early pace and tracked three wide along the first turn, was guided to the two path into the backstretch run and was well placed heading to the far turn, came in a bit tight nearing the quarter marker and moved out to the three path nearing the top of the lane, rallied approaching mid-stretch and shifted to the four path for the final furlong, responded to firm urging into the final sixteenth, surged in deep stretch and won the nod on the wire to prevail. MADEIRA WINE broke alertly and established the early advantage, set modest fractions while well rated through the backstretch run, showed the way to the quarter marker and extended the lead into upper stretch, was kept to task under steady urging to the sixteenth-marker, held foes at bay into deep stretch and was nailed at the finish for the win, while just holding for second. CLOCKSTRIKESTWELVE settled off of the early pace while not far back, advanced along the backstretch run and tracked the modest fractions from the inside, continued to gain ground into the second turn, shifted two wide for the drive, closed willingly inside of the furlong marker, vied between rivals into the final sixteenth and was outfinished for the win and place in the final strides. ASSIGNATION stalked the early pace, went two wide along the first turn then advanced to attend to the modest pace through the backstretch run, kept close attendance to the pacesetter to the quarter marker, shifted three wide nearing mid-stretch and chased to the furlong marker, lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was outkicked. COUNCILWOMAN JILLY was prominent in the early running and stalked the pace while three wide into the first turn, lost position along the backstretch run and gave chase while three wide into the far turn, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, could not keep pace heading to the furlong marker and weakened. TWILIGHT EMPIRE was allowed to settle, maintained a two wide path through the backstretch run, trailed into the far turn and came three wide to the quarter marker, swung widest for the stretch drive and lacked a late rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Councilwoman Jilly
ENTRY.OWNER: Sido Racing Partners LLC Freeman Cassie and Freeman Keenan

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 6F All Weather Track CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMOOVE AS SILK broke in sharply at the start and made contact with ESCAPE THE HEAT then was allowed to settle near the back in the early going, started a bid from the nine-sixteenths marker, was even with the leaders at the head of the stretch, had a little trouble changing leads then straightened out and drew away to a handy win. ALL HALLOWS came away from the gate in good order and was content to track VALERIE to the turn, bid from the three-eighths pole, caught that foe at the top of the stretch, had the lead for a stride or two but was no match for the winner, while running on well to hold second by a clear margin. PLEASANT WARNING prompted the pace to the turn, waited a bit nearing the top of the lane, was still in contention at the top of the stretch while under a steady drive, could not match the top two down the lane but held position to the wire. PRESTIGIOUS was fractious in the gate, broke slowly then was slow into stride, found a rhythm midway down the backstretch and gained contact with the pack, then lost ground and fell back to last position through the turn, came under pressure from the five-sixteenths pole, stayed on the rail into the stretch then swung out to the five path nearing the eighth pole and gained some ground in the late going. ROUSING STAR broke well but was outrun from the start and fell back to last in the early running, angled over towards the rail to save ground, did not respond to strong handling and was one-paced to the finish. VALERIE broke sharply and sprinted to a clear lead with a pair in close pursuit, came under pressure passing the five-sixteenths pole, was unable to keep pace and faded down the lane. ESCAPE THE HEAT was bumped at the start by SMOOVE AS SILK then chased the pace while racing wide to the turn, was done after a half mile and had nothing to offer in the stretch run.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 77. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOVIETIME was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the decent pace from a two wide path through the backstretch run, was roused along the far turn and confronted APPLE WARRIOR at the quarter marker, battled with that rival to mid-stretch then took command leaving the furlong marker, felt pressure from the oncoming runner-up into deep stretch, dug in while all out in the final strides and gamely lasted for the win at the finish. WAY TOO HOT was forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the decent pace while well placed through the backstretch run, gained ground along the far turn then came in tight and waited for racing room nearing the top of the stretch, angled three wide into the drive, ran evenly to mid-stretch, rallied inside of the furlong pole, put pressure on MOVIETIME into deep stretch but could not get by the game winner and just missed for the win, while besting the rest. APPLE WARRIOR was hustled away from the gate and dictated terms into the first turn, controlled the pace through the backstretch run while carving decent fractions, came under pressure from MOVIETIME at the quarter marker, met that bid to the furlong pole, could not keep pace with MOVIETIME into deep stretch, weakened and just held for third at the finish. TRIBUTE TO M hesitated leaving the start, was away slowly and spotted the field in the early running, was steered three wide into the first turn and settled through the backstretch run, was coaxed along three wide into the far turn, swung five wide for the drive, offered a mild late bid in the late stages and just missed for third. GRACEFUL MISCHIEF was unhurried in the early stages, settled inside while trailing through the backstretch run, was guided four wide into the far turn then came six wide for the stretch run, showed late interest in the stretch and improved position in the final furlong. CANTILEVER settled in the second flight leaving the start, tracked the decent pace while two wide through the backstretch run then mounted a two wide bid approaching the quarter marker, ran evenly to the furlong pole, could not keep pace into the late stages and tired. GALLO DEL CIELO lunged at the start and was off a bit slowly, recovered and tracked the early pace from the second flight, maintained a three wide path through the backstretch run, made a mild gain along the far turn, could not sustain that run into the stretch and gave way in the final stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Tribute to M
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slowly,settled 3wide,5wide into stretch,mild late bid,mssd 3d

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 6F All Weather Track CR: 92. Allowance Purse 31000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowe d 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TESSA (GB) broke a step slowly at the start, recovered and rushed to contention heading to the half-mile marker, stalked from the inside along the turn then angled three wide into upper stretch, responded to firm handling at the furlong marker, took command inside of the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in the final stages to prevail. LADY'S SERMON chased the solid early pace while two wide and between runners, maintained that two wide position while between rivals along the turn, lost ground in upper stretch and shifted to the three path at the furlong marker, closed willingly while four wide in the final sixteenth and was up in the final strides to secure the place. PAPPY'S GIRL was prominent leaving the start and attended to the solid early pace, advanced to press the pace while two wide along the turn, battled with HONORABLE GAL into the stretch, vied for the lead inside of the furlong marker, could not match strides with TESSA in the final sixteenth and was just edged for second at the finish, while just holding for third. HONORABLE GAL was asked to show speed leaving the break and set a solid early pace, was pressed along the turn by PAPPY'S GIRL and battled with that rival into the stretch, vied for the lead inside of the furlong marker, could not muster the needed response in deep stretch, weakened and was just edged for the minor awards. TAMANTARI tracked the solid early pace while outside of rivals, improved position while three wide on the turn, swung five wide into the stretch and lost a bit of ground at the furlong marker, re-rallied in deep stretch but needed more in the end and was outkicked.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 89. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KO SAMUI (IRE) tracked the quick early fractions from the inside, raced closest to the leading pair down the backside then was coaxed along into the three path heading to the far turn, was roused four wide into the stretch and loomed at mid-stretch, took command inside of the furlong marker, was kept to task under a firm hand ride into deep stretch and held safely for the win. TABLE FOR TWO was unhurried while saving ground in the early stages, tracked from the second flight through the backstretch run and saved all of the ground to the far turn, made a steady bid into the stretch and tipped two wide for the drive, came in a bit tight at the furlong marker while held up behind the tiring pacesetter, ran in pursuit of KO SAMUI into deep stretch, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and held for second. QUALITY CAT settled in the second flight, tracked the quick pace while outside of a rival through the backstretch run, saved ground along the far turn, came in tight approaching the furlong marker, steadied while in traffic then was blocked heading to the final sixteenth, found room in deep stretch and closed in time to secure the show. ZOOKEEPER disputed the solid early pace with WICKLOW HILLS, assumed command into the backstretch run and set quick fractions into the far turn, showed the way into upper stretch, was collared by the winner at the furlong marker, yielded in deep stretch and was just edged for third in the final strides. LORD OF LIGHT settled in the two path in the early running, maintained that two wide position while settling into the far turn, rallied in upper stretch, came in a bit tight inside of the furlong marker and was outkicked in the final sixteenth. WICKLOW HILLS broke alertly and contested the early pace with ZOOKEEPER, conceded the lead along the backstretch run and stalked that rival through solid fractions to the half-mile pole, gave chase while two wide along the far turn, vied for the lead into upper stretch, could not hold off oncoming rivals in the final furlong and weakened. SGT POWELL settled in the second flight in the early going, tracked the solid pace while two wide through the backstretch run, gained ground while four wide along the far turn, mounted a four wide bid into the stretch but needed more in the final stages. HOT JOURNEY settled in mid-pack in the early running, raced three then four wide into the backstretch run, improved position heading to the half-mile marker, mounted a five wide bid into the stretch, could not sustain that run in the final furlong and flattened out. SIPPIN WHISKEY settled three wide into the first turn, slipped to the inside approaching the second turn and did not threaten in the stretch. DARK MYSTERY settled in the two path early on, lost position along the backstretch run and did not factor. COACH OTT was unhurried leaving the break, trailed to the far turn and did not make an impact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 91. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden, C laiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RALLY CAT was hustled out of the gate, dueled with STRETCH RUN down the backstretch, backed off the pace going into the turn, re-rallied from the five-sixteenths, battled for a furlong down the lane, got the best of that one near the furlong marker and just lasted over a pair closing fast on the outside. R M C HOOK'EM came away from the gate in good order and was between a trio of horses tracking the pace duel, began a three wide rally from the three eighths pole, hooked up with REFI NOW down the stretch, was gaining on the eventual winner in the final yards and won the nod for the place. REFI NOW broke well and took up a nice tracking spot behind the dueling leaders, saved ground through the turn but had nowhere to run until mid-stretch, tipped out to the two path and rallied with R M C HOOKEM to the outside and was out-bobbed for second. QUANTUM QUEST lunged at the start, then had to take up when GRIT AND CURIOSITY came over after the break, moved towards the inside for the backstretch run, was slowly making some forward progress through the turn, encountered traffic passing the three-eighths pole, swung five wide into the stretch and ran on once clear. BOSS OF THEMOSS broke a step or two slowly then moved up along the rail, was hard to place while getting into contention going into the turn, lost some momentum when checked near the seven-sixteenths pole then was unable to make up the needed ground despite making a late run. STRETCH RUN was hard to load prior to the start, broke out at the start, then was hard sent to join the early pace, was joined by RALLY CAT early, then took command when that foe ceded the lead through the turn, battled back when that rival re-engaged at the top of the stretch then weakened with a furlong to run. IMPLICITLY broke well but lacked any speed, was being pushed by the rider while chasing the pack through the turn, tipped out seven or eight wide into the stretch and finished with some interest. AMANOFMYSTATURE broke well and was ridden from the break, could not match the early pace and raced mid-pack and in the five path down the backstretch, tried to rally under a drive through the turn, came into the stretch seven wide and was unable to improve position. GRIT AND CURIOSITY broke inward a bit and into the path of QUANTUM QUEST, fell far behind in the early going, stayed on the rail to the stretch, was kept to task and managed to pass one inside the furlong pole. DR PESCADO broke well and was on the outside of the tracking trio down the backstretch, continued wide around the turn, made a mild bid from the three-eighths pole, swung five to six wide into the stretch then was unable to keep pace in the final furlong.
